70:"To enable the Virtual Background feature for all users in the account.";i:6;s:92:"Sign in to the Zoom web portal as an administrator with permission to edit account settings.";i:7;s:70:"In the navigation menu click Account Management then Account Settings.";i:8;s:61:"In the Meeting tab navigate to the Virtual Background option.";i:9;s:112:"The Virtual Background feature allows you to display an image or video as your background during a Zoom Meeting.";i:10;s:44:"In this video we will cover how to enable a.";i:11;s:75:"Zoom allows you to use your own Virtual Background during Conference calls.";i:12;s:23:"No Green Screen needed.";i:13;s:57:"Simply follow the steps in this video and in no time you.";i:14;s:259:"Turn on Virtual Background During a Meeting While in a Zoom meeting click the up arrow next to StartStop Video Click Choose a Virtual Background Select one of the available images to use as your virtual background or click Add Image to upload one of your own.";i:15;s:78:"Open the Zoom app or enter your meeting click on zoomus and click Preferences.";i:16;s:50:"Select Virtual Background on the menu to the left.";i:17;s:117:"There are a few default background options that you can choose fromby clicking on one it will change your background.";i:18;s:108:"To add or change your virtual background during a meeting click on the upward arrow next to StartStop Video.";i:19;s:67:"Click Choose Virtual Background and select any of your backgrounds.";i:20;s:56:"Top 3 tips for the best Zoom Virtual Background results.";i:21;s:135:"Click Choose Virtual Background Now you can pick one of the 2 video background that Zoom provides you or you can upload your own video.";i:22;s:32:"Enable Zoom Virtual Backgrounds.";i:23;s:67:"First open the Zoom web portal and access your account information.";i:24;s:46:"Next choose Settings then In Meeting Advanced.";i:25;s:73:"Last enable the Virtual background setting so that the button turns blue.";i:26;s:31:"Open a Blank Canvas in Kapwing.";i:27;s:42:"Simply tap one to make it your background.";i:28;s:79:"To use a custom virtual background scroll over to the right and tap the button.";i:29;s:74:"Zoom will open a file manager and you can select any image on your device.";i:30;s:52:"Zoom for Android does not support video backgrounds.";i:31;s:59:"Once you select an image it will appear as your background.";i:32;s:137:"The holy-grail solution to generating a great virtual background is to place a green screen behind you that spans your entire background.";i:33;s:74:"Then Zoom will create a beautiful chroma-keyed background using the green.";i:34;s:83:"The other option is to let Zoom figure it out without the benefit of a solid color.";i:35;s:86:"It works but often with the edges of your head and body shimmering like an apparition.";i:36;s:80:"Maybe some people dont care how solid they appear with their virtual background.";i:37;s:89:"With Settings open you should see Virtual Background about halfway down on the left side.";i:38;s:97:"Click on that and youll see either the Virtual Background page Figure B or the warning that your.";i:39;s:26:"Heres what you need to do.";i:40;s:54:"Go to zoomusprofile and click on Settings on the left.";i:41;s:79:"Scroll down to the In Meeting Advanced section and look for Virtual Background.";i:42;s:68:"Click the button to add a new background and choose your background.";i:43;s:68:"Click the button to add a new background and choose your background.";i:44;s:104:"Please note that Zoom sometimes has a mirroring effectwhile your background may appear backwards to you.";i:45;s:56:"The best Zoom background image size is 1920px by 1080px.";i:46;s:31:"This is an aspect ratio of 169.";i:47;s:107:"Zoom states that using other dimensions may result in black bars cropping out the virtual background image.";i:48;s:87:"A couple other requirements you should note about your Zoom virtual background include.";i:49;s:50:"Zoom background photo should be under 5MB in size.";i:50;s:112:"The virtual background feature allows you to display an image or video as your background during a Zoom Meeting.";i:51;s:136:"This feature works best with a green screen and uniform lighting to allow Zoom to detect the difference between you and your background.";i:52;s:70:"You can also upload your own images or videos as a virtual background.";i:53;s:21:"Should be super easy.";i:54;s:181:"Open up any graphics editor even Paint on Windows create a blank image thats around 1000 x 700 then fill it with the color you want and select it in Zoom as your virtual background.";i:55;s:90:"In the Settings window click on the Virtual Background tab on the left side of the window.";i:56;s:90:"To set a video background in Zoom click on a thumbnail marked with a icon see image below.";i:57;s:67:"Zoom provides a couple of videos itself in the app but you can add.";}}